ZH: 我因为堵车迟到了，耽误了早上的会议。
EN: I was late because of the traffic jam, which delayed the morning meeting.

ZH: 我担心他的懒散会耽误我们的计划。
EN: I'm worried that his laziness will hinder our plans.

ZH: 别为了小事情耽误了整个进度。
EN: Don't let small things hold up the entire process.

ZH: 这次恶劣的天气耽误了很多航班。
EN: The bad weather has caused a lot of flight delays.

ZH: 快点，别耽误了下一班地铁。
EN: Hurry up, don't miss the next subway train.

ZH: 我不想因为他的错误而耽误自己的事业。
EN: I don't want to let his mistake hinder my career.

ZH: 我们不能因为一点挫折就被耽误了前进的脚步。
EN: We can't let a setback hinder our progress.

ZH: 不要再玩手机了，否则会耽误学习。
EN: Stop playing with your phone, otherwise it will delay your studying.

ZH: 需要付出额外的努力，但不要耽误自己的轨道。
EN: It takes extra effort, but don't let it derail you.

ZH: 他的拖延会耽误整个团队的进展。
EN: His procrastination will delay the progress of the entire team.

ZH: 这个工作会耽误我和家人相聚的时间。
EN: This job will take away the time I could spend with my family.

ZH: 不要让困难耽误你追求梦想的决心。
EN: Don't let difficulties hinder your determination to pursue your dreams.

ZH: 我不想错过这个机会，不想被耽误了。
EN: I don't want to miss this opportunity, I don't want to be delayed.

ZH: 我的困惑耽误了我做出决策的时间。
EN: My confusion delayed the time for me to make a decision.

ZH: 他的拖拉耽误了整个计划的执行。
EN: His laziness delayed the execution of the entire plan.

ZH: 那个同事经常迟到，耽误了工作进度。
EN: That colleague is frequently late, which delays the progress of work.

ZH: 老师的迟到耽误了我们上课的时间。
EN: The teacher's late arrival delayed our class time.

ZH: 病情的恶化一直耽误着他的康复进程。
EN: The worsening of the illness has been delaying his recovery process.

ZH: 这场雨会耽误我们户外活动的计划。
EN: This rain will delay our outdoor activities plan.

ZH: 这个项目的滞后会耽误整个公司的发展。
EN: The delay in this project will hinder the development of the entire company.
